<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../style.css" type="text/css" media="all"/>
  <title>ED(1)</title>
</head>
<body>
<table class="head">
  <tr>
    <td class="head-ltitle">ED(1)</td>
    <td class="head-vol">General Commands Manual</td>
    <td class="head-rtitle">ED(1)</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<div class="manual-text">
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="NAME"><a class="permalink" href="#NAME">NAME</a></h1>
<p class="Pp"><code class="Nm">ed</code> &#x2014; <span class="Nd">the standard
    line-oriented text editor</span></p>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="SYNOPSIS"><a class="permalink" href="#SYNOPSIS">SYNOPSIS</a></h1>
<table class="Nm">
  <tr>
    <td><code class="Nm">ed</code></td>
    <td>[<code class="Fl">-p</code> <var class="Ar">prompt</var>]
      [<var class="Ar">file</var>]</td>
  </tr>
</table>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="DESCRIPTION"><a class="permalink" href="#DESCRIPTION">DESCRIPTION</a></h1>
<p class="Pp">The <code class="Nm">ed</code> utility is a line-oriented text
    editor. It operates in two modes:
    <a class="permalink" href="#command"><i class="Em" id="command">command
    mode</i></a> and
    <a class="permalink" href="#input"><i class="Em" id="input">input
    mode</i></a>. In command mode, <code class="Nm">ed</code> reads commands
    from standard input and executes them to manipulate the contents of a
    buffer. When in input mode, <code class="Nm">ed</code> appends text to the
    buffer.</p>
<p class="Pp">If a <var class="Ar">file</var> argument is given,
    <code class="Nm">ed</code> simulates an <code class="Ic">e</code> command on
    the file before reading commands from standard input.</p>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="ADDRESSING"><a class="permalink" href="#ADDRESSING">ADDRESSING</a></h1>
<p class="Pp">Commands operate on zero, one, or two addresses. A address
    represents a line number in the buffer.</p>
<dl class="Bl-tag">
  <dt>.</dt>
  <dd>The current line (dot).</dd>
  <dt id="$"><a class="permalink" href="#$"><code class="Li">$</code></a></dt>
  <dd>The last line in the buffer.</dd>
  <dt id="n"><a class="permalink" href="#n"><code class="Li">n</code></a></dt>
  <dd>The n-th line in the buffer.</dd>
  <dt id="'x"><a class="permalink" href="#'x"><code class="Li">'x</code></a></dt>
  <dd>The line marked with the character <var class="Ar">x</var> via the
      <code class="Ic">k</code> command.</dd>
  <dt id="+n"><a class="permalink" href="#+n"><code class="Li">+n</code></a>,
    <code class="Li">-n</code></dt>
  <dd>Relative offset of <var class="Ar">n</var> lines from the preceding
      address.</dd>
  <dt>,</dt>
  <dd>Equivalent to <code class="Li">1,$</code>.</dd>
  <dt>;</dt>
  <dd>Equivalent to <code class="Li">.,$</code>, but sets dot to the first
      address before calculating the second.</dd>
</dl>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="COMMANDS"><a class="permalink" href="#COMMANDS">COMMANDS</a></h1>
<p class="Pp"><code class="Nm">ed</code> supports the following commands:</p>
<dl class="Bl-tag">
  <dt>(addr) <code class="Ic">a</code></dt>
  <dd>Append text after the addressed line. Input is terminated by a single
      period on a line.</dd>
  <dt>(addr1,addr2) <code class="Ic">d</code></dt>
  <dd>Delete the addressed lines. Dot is set to the line following the deleted
      range.</dd>
  <dt id="h"><a class="permalink" href="#h"><code class="Ic">h</code></a></dt>
  <dd>Print the last error message.</dd>
  <dt id="H"><a class="permalink" href="#H"><code class="Ic">H</code></a></dt>
  <dd>Toggle the automatic printing of error messages.</dd>
  <dt>(addr1,addr2) <code class="Ic">j</code></dt>
  <dd>Join the addressed lines into a single line.</dd>
  <dt>(addr) <code class="Ic">k</code> <var class="Ar">x</var></dt>
  <dd>Mark the addressed line with the character <var class="Ar">x</var>.</dd>
  <dt>(addr1,addr2) <code class="Ic">n</code></dt>
  <dd>Print the addressed lines prefixed by their line numbers and a tab.</dd>
  <dt>(addr1,addr2) <code class="Ic">p</code></dt>
  <dd>Print the addressed lines.</dd>
  <dt id="P"><a class="permalink" href="#P"><code class="Ic">P</code></a></dt>
  <dd>Toggle the command prompt character.</dd>
  <dt id="q"><a class="permalink" href="#q"><code class="Ic">q</code></a></dt>
  <dd>Quit <code class="Nm">ed</code>. If the buffer has been modified since the
      last write, a warning is issued.</dd>
  <dt>(addr1,addr2) <code class="Ic">s/re/replacement/g</code></dt>
  <dd>Substitute <var class="Ar">replacement</var> for the regular expression
      <var class="Ar">re</var> in the addressed lines.</dd>
  <dt>(addr1,addr2) <code class="Ic">w</code> [<var class="Ar">file</var>]</dt>
  <dd>Write the addressed lines to <var class="Ar">file</var>.</dd>
</dl>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="ERRORS"><a class="permalink" href="#ERRORS">ERRORS</a></h1>
<p class="Pp">When an error occurs, <code class="Nm">ed</code> prints a
    &#x2018;<code class="Li"></code>&#x2019;? and returns to command mode. The
    <code class="Ic">h</code> command can be used to view the specific
  error.</p>
</section>
<section class="Sh">
<h1 class="Sh" id="SEE_ALSO"><a class="permalink" href="#SEE_ALSO">SEE
  ALSO</a></h1>
<p class="Pp"><a class="Xr" href="../html1/cat.html">cat(1)</a>,
    <a class="Xr" href="../html1/vi.html">vi(1)</a>,
    <a class="Xr" href="../html7/regex.html">regex(7)</a></p>
</section>
</div>
